isNested

public static boolean isNested(String str,
                               int index,
                               String openBalance,
                               String closeBalance)
                        throws IllegalArgumentException
Returns true if the character in the index parameter is nested inside balanced characters. for example, using the String "a(b,c),(d,e[f]),g'abcdefg'": isNested(str, 0, "(['",")]'") will return false while the same call with an index of 3 will return true. The length of openBalance must be exactly the same as the length of closeBalance. each character in openBalance is paired with the character of the same index in closeBalance. For example if openBalance="([" closeBalance should be ")]" if the same type of brackets are to be paired.

Parameters:
str - The String that will be parsed
index - The index of the character that will be checked.
openBalance - A String containing all the balance opening characters.
closeBalance - A String containing all the balance closing characters.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException
